Short answer: **yes**. Your stylesheet is already solid, but there’s still meaningful redundancy and a few specificity/consistency issues that we can eliminate without changing markup. Below I’ll (1) point out the most impactful refactor targets, then (2) give you a **drop‑in patch** that consolidates common patterns, introduces layers/tokens/utilities, and removes duplication—while keeping all your existing class names and behavior intact. fileciteturn0file0

---

## What to refactor (highest impact first)

1) **Consolidate identical button patterns**  
` .hero-cta` and `.btn-pill` share the same structure (display, radius, transitions, active press). Merge their shared rules with low‑specificity grouping selectors, and keep per‑component tokens for colors. This cuts repetition and avoids diverging behavior. fileciteturn0file0

2) **Centralize container widths, radii, shadows, and spacing**  
You repeat values like `max-width: min(1160px, 92vw)`, `border-radius: 16px/18px/30px`, and several box‑shadows across sections (`.program-media`, testimonial cards, split images, form/card surfaces). Define canonical tokens (e.g., `--container`, `--radius-l`, `--shadow-2`) and reuse. fileciteturn0file0

3) **Prefer logical properties consistently**  
You already use some (`inline-size`), but many blocks still mix `width/height/padding:` with logical counterparts (e.g., `.program-media`, `.brand`, `.mobile-menu`, `.header`). Unifying on logical properties (`inline-size`, `block-size`, `padding-inline`, `border-block-end`) simplifies RTL / vertical writing-mode support “for free.” fileciteturn0file0

4) **Reduce global `:focus-visible` side effects**  
You set a global `:focus-visible` outline **and** component‑level outlines (hero CTA, contact links, dots). Move to a single focus ring utility to avoid fighting outlines and the `!important` you had to add on testimonial dots. fileciteturn0file0

5) **Group identical media queries**  
You repeat blocks for the same min‑widths across components (`600/700/768/900/1200px`). Group them (still pure CSS) to make breakpoints auditable, or lean further into `clamp()` to avoid some breakpoints entirely (you’re already partway there). fileciteturn0file0

6) **Nix scattered image resets and `!important`**  
Central `img{display:block;max-inline-size:100%;}` covers most repeated image rules. Keep component overrides where necessary (hero media can keep `object-fit:cover` and needs no `!important` if specificity is handled). fileciteturn0file0

---

## Drop‑in refactor patch (additive, low risk)

> Paste the block below **after** your current variables (or at the very top if you prefer) and remove the noted duplicates where called out. It uses `@layer` to keep cascade predictable and `:where()` to keep specificity low. No HTML changes required.

```css
/* ===== Base layering so future merges stay predictable ===== */
@layer reset, tokens, base, components, utilities;

/* ===== TOKENS (augment your existing :root) ===== */
@layer tokens {
  :root {
    /* Layout + rhythm */
    --container: min(1160px, 92vw);
    --container-narrow: min(980px, 90vw);

    /* Radii */
    --radius-s: 6px;
    --radius-m: 12px;
    --radius-l: 16px;
    --radius-xl: 18px;
    --radius-pill: 30px;

    /* Shadows (reuse across cards/media/buttons) */
    --shadow-1: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
    --shadow-2: 0 10px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
    --shadow-3: 0 12px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22);

    /* Focus ring */
    --focus-ring-color: var(--primary);
    --focus-ring: 3px solid var(--focus-ring-color);
    --focus-ring-offset: 2px;
  }

  :root[data-theme="dark"] {
    /* Dark keeps same geometry, just reuse your color tokens */
    --shadow-1: 0 2px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
    --shadow-2: 0 10px 24px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.18);
    --shadow-3: 0 12px 28px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22);
  }
}

/* ===== BASE: normalize a few repeated patterns ===== */
@layer base {
  /* Global media reset (lets you remove many repeated img rules) */
  img {
    display: block;
    max-inline-size: 100%;
    block-size: auto;
  }

  /* Sensible, consistent focus treatment */
  :where(a, button, input, textarea, select, summary, [role="button"]):focus-visible {
    outline: var(--focus-ring);
    outline-offset: var(--focus-ring-offset);
  }

  /* A generic "container" constraint to replace repeated max-widths */
  .container,
  :where(.section--testimonials .t-wrap,
         .section--programs .programs-grid) {
    max-inline-size: var(--container);
    margin-inline: auto;
  }

  /* Even/odd backgrounds by section already exist;
     make the section itself consistent */
  .section {
    inline-size: 100%;
    padding-block: 36px; /* replaces padding: 36px 0 */
    content-visibility: auto;
    contain-intrinsic-size: 500px;
    text-align: center;
  }
}

/* ===== COMPONENT CONSOLIDATIONS ===== */
@layer components {
  /* 1) Buttons: .hero-cta and .btn-pill share 90% of rules */
  :where(.hero-cta, .btn-pill) {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 12px 28px;
    border-radius: var(--radius-pill);
    line-height: 1.2;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: background 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease, transform 0.06s ease-in-out;
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px color-mix(in srgb, var(--text) 20%, transparent), var(--shadow-1);
    font-weight: 700; /* unify weights */
  }
  /* Keep each component’s own color tokens */
  .hero-cta {
    background: var(--hero-cta-bg);
    color: var(--hero-cta-text);
    font-size: clamp(1.06rem, 0.6rem + 1vw, 1.375rem);
  }
  .btn-pill {
    background: var(--cta-bg);
    color: var(--cta-text);
    border: 0;
    font-size: clamp(1.02rem, 0.9rem + 0.5vw, 1.2rem);
  }
  :where(.hero-cta, .btn-pill):hover,
  :where(.hero-cta, .btn-pill):focus-visible {
    background: var(--cta-hover-bg, var(--hero-cta-hover-bg));
    color: var(--cta-hover-text, var(--hero-cta-hover-text));
  }
  :where(.hero-cta, .btn-pill):active { transform: translateY(1px); }

  /* 2) Cards/surfaces share look (form + testimonial + program media) */
  :where(.section--testimonials .t-card,
         .section--programs .program-media,
         .contact-form,
         .contact-card) {
    border-radius: var(--radius-xl);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-2);
  }
  .section--programs .program-media { overflow: hidden; }

  /* 3) Testimonial dots: drop the !important by using a slightly higher, but still low, specificity grouping */
  .section--testimonials .t-dot::before {
    content: "";
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    margin: auto;
    inline-size: 10px;
    block-size: 10px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--t-dot-fill);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--t-dot-ring);
    transition: transform 0.12s ease, box-shadow 0.12s ease, background-color 0.12s ease;
  }
  .section--testimonials .t-dot[aria-selected="true"]::before {
    background: var(--t-dot-active);
    box-shadow: 0 0 0 2px var(--t-dot-ring);
  }
  .section--testimonials .t-dot:hover::before { transform: scale(1.15); }
  .section--testimonials .t-dot:focus-visible {
    outline: var(--focus-ring);
    outline-offset: 2px;
  }

  /* 4) Logical properties for header + footer quick wins */
  .header {
    position: sticky;
    inset-block-start: 0;        /* replaces top: 0 */
    padding-inline: 16px;        /* replaces padding: 0 16px */
    block-size: 56px;            /* replaces height */
  }
  .footer {
    padding-block: 24px 16px;    /* replaces padding: 24px 0 16px 0 */
    text-align: center;
  }

  /* 5) Mobile menu: prefer logical sizing & transform */
  .mobile-menu {
    inset-block-start: 0;
    inset-inline-end: 0;         /* replaces right: 0 */
    inline-size: 80vw;
    max-inline-size: 340px;
    block-size: 100vh;
    transform: translateX(100%);
  }
  .mobile-menu.active { transform: translateX(0); }
}

/* ===== UTILITIES (opt-in, low specificity) ===== */
@layer utilities {
  /* Generic focus utility for places you want a stronger ring */
  .u-focus-strong:focus-visible {
    outline: 4px solid var(--focus-ring-color);
    outline-offset: 3px;
  }

  /* Centered container constraint you can attach if the markup already has .container */
  .u-container { max-inline-size: var(--container); margin-inline: auto; }

  /* Spacing helpers (small sample) */
  .u-stack-12 > * + * { margin-block-start: 12px; }

  /* Text truncation helper (for brand title, hero title) */
  .u-ellipsis {
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
  }
}
```

### Safe removals / merges after adding the patch
- **Buttons**: Remove duplicated display/transition/active rules in `.hero-cta` and `.btn-pill`; keep only their color tokens and size differences. (The patch already provides the shared style.) fileciteturn0file0  
- **Image `display:block`**: Remove repeated `img { display:block; width:100%; height:auto; }` clones inside components; the base rule now covers it. Keep hero media’s `object-fit` rule. fileciteturn0file0  
- **Testimonials dots**: You can drop the `!important` on `.t-dot::before` shadows after this, because the refactor gives them a clean, consistent focus/selected spec. fileciteturn0file0  
- **Logical props**: Where I showed logical replacements (header, mobile menu, footer), you can remove the old physical properties to avoid drift. fileciteturn0file0

---

## Additional targeted cleanups (optional, but worth it)

- **Replace physical borders with logical**  
  e.g., `.mobile-menu .nav-item { border-bottom: 1px solid var(--divider); }` → `border-block-end: 1px solid var(--divider);`. This is a mechanical change and improves i18n/RTL resilience. fileciteturn0file0

- **Container variables**  
  Replace repeated `max-width: min(1160px, 92vw)` / `min(1160px, 86vw)` with `var(--container)` and, where needed, a `--container-narrow` override (sample variable included). You use those sizes in `.section--programs .programs-grid`, `.section--testimonials .t-wrap`, and `.section--split .split`. fileciteturn0file0

- **Unify card radii**  
  You mix `16px` and `18px` across cards and media; decide on `--radius-l`/`--radius-xl` and apply consistently. You’ll immediately see a more coherent system look. fileciteturn0file0

- **Focus system**  
  You currently define per-component focus outlines (hero links, contact links, dots) and a global `:focus-visible`. Replace per‑component outlines with the new `--focus-ring` or `.u-focus-strong` utility to avoid specificity battles. fileciteturn0file0

- **Clamp rationalization**  
  Many font sizes already use `clamp()`. A few still re‑declare font sizes again inside media queries (e.g., testimonials title/dots/buttons at `401/421px`). You can fold these into a single `clamp()` to remove those media blocks entirely without visual change. fileciteturn0file0

---

## Why this is forward‑compatible

- **`@layer`** keeps future additions from accidentally overriding base styles.  
- **Logical properties** future‑proof you for RTL/vertical writing modes.  
- **Component tokens** (kept for CTA colors) preserve theming flexibility you already set up with `data-theme`.  
- **No new dependencies** and no HTML changes.

---

## Expected payoff

- **~15–25% stylesheet shrink** from grouping buttons, removing duplicated image rules, and centralizing container/radius/shadow tokens.  
- **Lower specificity & fewer `!important`s**, which reduces regression risk.  
- **Cleaner theming** (dark/light) because you separate “system” tokens from component tokens.

If you want, I can produce a **fully merged file** (not just the patch) that inlines the removals above and applies the logical‑property conversions throughout your specific selectors; but even adopting just the patch will give you most of the win immediately. fileciteturn0file0

---

If you disagree with any of the consolidations (e.g., you intentionally wanted `.hero-cta` hover timing to differ from `.btn-pill`), call it out and we’ll preserve that divergence while still removing the rest of the duplication.
